<span id="freeTextContainer16699153828429941669">I absolutely loved this book and will never think about gender relations in China the same way. I was skeptical about gender equality there after my own experience, but Hong Fincher shows how much greater that disparity has become in the last decade since the property boom and new laws came into being. The book flowed well and was well organized. It was less about the leftover women themselves than what it would mean to be without a spouse in China or how women go into marriages so they can own </span>
  <span id="freeText16699153828429941669" style="display:none">I absolutely loved this book and will never think about gender relations in China the same way. I was skeptical about gender equality there after my own experience, but Hong Fincher shows how much greater that disparity has become in the last decade since the property boom and new laws came into being. The book flowed well and was well organized. It was less about the leftover women themselves than what it would mean to be without a spouse in China or how women go into marriages so they can own property, yet it’s never really theirs. This is a quick read and one you won’t forget. Looking forward to her new book later this year.</span>
