  <span id="freeText16879620781717728344" style="display:none">I’m Filipino, and don’t normally pay attention to what happens in other Asian countries. I prefer Filipino authors, writing about Filipino experiences. BUT I’m really glad I picked up this book. In the book, you learn what Chinese women face in the uniquely oppressive cultural discrepancy in China. Their empowerment by being a woman affected by the passage of time, and the shifting roles of power from the Song, Ming dynasties, to socialism in 1949, to post-Mao Zedong....I hope in the years to come, more legislation is passed for women to gain more property rights, and for a paradigm shift to happen in regards to how the society/government/culture approaches what is or isn’t acceptable for women there to do </span>
